resolution: Verified the runtime provider/adapter source classifier and pm health surfacing already satisfy GH-244; closing the stale tracking item.
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-18T21:58:24.218Z",claude-code-agent,"Triage (during pm-ldr1/GH-157 work): GH-244 is CLOSED on GitHub — resolved in #254 (commit 0447c6e4) by surfacing provider_source/vector_store_source + persisted *_configured values in pm health, so auto-detected providers are no longer misreported as 'not configured'. The narrower 'persist the resolved provider/adapter strings back into settings.json' idea is DECLINED: writing settings.json on every read risks the governance persist-trap (cf pm-haak file-backed-schema leak) and churns the file under VCS. Recommend closing as resolved-by-#254 in a NON-release-bearing touch (closing here would mis-bucket the changelog since the fix already shipped). Related: [[pm-ldr1]] search ergonomics."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-19T20:57:11.856Z",claude-code-agent,"Verified GH-244 is already fully implemented and the GitHub issue is CLOSED. resolveProviderConfigSource() (src/core/search/providers.ts:61) classifies configured|auto-detected|unconfigured, and pm health surfaces provider_configured/provider_source + vector_store_configured/vector_store_source in the vectorization check (src/cli/commands/health.ts:1518-1533), so a config audit can tell an auto-detected empty provider/adapter apart from a genuine misconfiguration. No code change required."
close_reason: "Already shipped: GH-244 implemented via resolveProviderConfigSource + pm health provider_source/vector_store_source surfacing; GitHub issue #244 is CLOSED. Verified in this session, no further code change needed."
body: ""
